abstract: Anne Sacoolas pleaded guilty on Thursday to causing the death of Harry Dunn, a 19-year-old British motorcyclist, in 2019, when she was a State Department employee in England.
snippet: Anne Sacoolas pleaded guilty on Thursday to causing the death of Harry Dunn, a 19-year-old British motorcyclist, in 2019, when she was a State Department employee in England.
lead_paragraph: Anne Sacoolas, an American who fled Britain in 2019 after her car fatally struck a 19-year-old British motorcyclist in central England, pleaded guilty on Thursday to causing the death of the teenager, Harry Dunn, by careless driving, British prosecutors said.

main: American Woman Pleads Guilty in Death of British Teenager
print_headline: American Woman Pleads Guilty In Death of Teenager in Britain

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Tuesday, May 2, 2023.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Tuesday, May 2, 2023.
lead_paragraph: An article on April 23 about donations from the Sackler family to the National Academies of Sciences, Engineering and Medicine referred imprecisely to statistics from the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention on the number of adults in the United States with chronic pain. Roughly 52 million adults suffered from chronic pain, according to a C.D.C. report, and of those, more than 17 million U.S. adults experience high-impact or more severe chronic pain; the number of U.S. adults affected by chronic pain does not range between 17 million and 52 million people. The error was repeated in a follow-up article on Sunday.

Putin is facing six months after he ordered the invasion of Ukraine.

main: Russia Accuses Ukraine of a Murder, and Hawks Demand Vengeance

abstract: At a pivotal moment as a counteroffensive makes gains, the secretary of state pledged $2.8 billion more in military aid to Ukraine and allies.
snippet: At a pivotal moment as a counteroffensive makes gains, the secretary of state pledged $2.8 billion more in military aid to Ukraine and allies.
lead_paragraph: RZESZOW, POLAND  Secretary of State Antony J. Blinken paid a surprise visit to Kyiv on Thursday, pledging $2.8 billion in military aid for Ukraine and other countries at risk of Russian invasion as the United States backs a Ukrainian effort to gain fresh military momentum.

main: In a Surprise Visit to Ukraine, Blinken Offers Aid and Encouragement

abstract: Readers react to Pamela Pauls argument that some diversity efforts have been misguided.
snippet: Readers react to Pamela Pauls argument that some diversity efforts have been misguided.

lead_paragraph: Nick Bostroms 2014 book, Superintelligence, a crucial text for the community of worriers about the risks of artificial intelligence, begins with a fable: A tribe of sparrows, weary of a marginal existence, becomes convinced that everything would be better if they could only have an owl to help them out  to build nests, to assist with care and feeding, to keep an eye out for other predators. Delighted by this idea, the sparrows decide to go hunting for an owl egg or owl chick that they might bring up as their own.
